nts_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-10-27T18:08:36Z","updated_at":"2025-10-27T18:08:36Z","body":"We were looking at this in a meeting and just wanted to share some other interesting size discrepancies we noticed:\n\n```py\nimport streamlit as st\n\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=29)\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=30)\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=31)\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=50)\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=100)\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=150)\nst.text_area(\"Hello\", width=\"stretch\", height=200)\n```\n\n<img width=\"814\" height=\"1138\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/80a83093-c4ee-4d78-96e9-665504dbfa08\" />\n","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/comments/3452653172/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"sfc-gh-bnisco","id":178842601,"node_id":"U_kgDOCqjr6Q","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/178842601?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco","html_url":"https://github.com/sfc-gh-bnisco","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-bnisco/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/comments/3452939796","html_url":"https://github.com/streamlit/streamlit/issues/12867#issuecomment-3452939796","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/12867","id":3452939796,"node_id":"IC_kwDODCoeTs7Nz64U","user":{"login":"sfc-gh-lwilby","id":103002751,"node_id":"U_kgDOBiOyfw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/103002751?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby","html_url":"https://github.com/sfc-gh-lwilby","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-10-27T19:25:22Z","updated_at":"2025-10-27T19:33:22Z","body":"@sfc-gh-bnisco @sfc-gh-kmcgrady one thing to keep in mind is that `st.text_area` has some non-standard behaviour that was already in place before extending the height functionality and it makes it work differently than other elements.  \n\nThe minimum height for the element is measured according to the lines of text in the input so we don't allow heights that will give less than 2 lines of text in the input, so I think that explains a lot of what you are seeing here. The first one should also be 2 lines as well, however, so the boundary for this bug seems to be 29. \n\nI think 150 should be more than 2 lines of text, so I'm surprised by that. I will take a look at that as well!\n\nI think given the way the height has to be applied to this element, the bug is probably just some edge case issue with the calculations and not complex or anything. I just wanted to make sure these bugs are documented here so I can more easily keep track of them. ","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/comments/3452939796/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"sfc-gh-lwilby","id":103002751,"node_id":"U_kgDOBiOyfw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/103002751?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby","html_url":"https://github.com/sfc-gh-lwilby","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sfc-gh-lwilby/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"id":20534346853,"node_id":"MEE_lADODCoeTs7UBX1azwAAAATH8URl","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/events/20534346853","actor":{"login":"sfc-gh-kmcgrady","id":103003886,"